<paragraph id="D83D3697B87CEB039E50FA1CE333C7C5" blockId="7.[111,647,1484,1700]" lastBlockId="7.[675,1210,216,432]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">
<taxonomicName id="1F824D14B87CEB039E50FA1CE6BCC070" authority="Hampson, 1901" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1901" box="[113,423,1515,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Amaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apyga">
<emphasis id="EAF6EA85B87CEB039E50FA1CE7E1C071" box="[113,250,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">Amaxia apyga</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BC134B66B87CEB039EDEFA1CE6BCC070" author="HAMPSON G. F." box="[255,423,1515,1541]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" refId="ref19615" refString="HAMPSON G. F. 1901. - Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum 3. Printed by order of the Trustees, London: 690 p." type="book" year="1901">Hampson, 1901</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
est décrit à partir d’un mâle unique des Monts Candelaria au 
<collectingCountry id="A0957607B87CEB039C28F9FCE59FC051" box="[521,644,1546,1573]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
. Il est mis en synonymie par 
<bibRefCitation id="BC134B66B87CEB039F80F9DDE54AC031" author="TOULGOET H. &amp; DE" box="[417,593,1578,1604]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" pagination="179 - 186" refId="ref20498" refString="TOULGOET H. DE 1989. - Description de nouvelles Arctiides neotropicales et contribution a la revision du genre Amaxia Walker, 1855 (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae Arctiinae) (30 e note). Nouvelle Revue d'Entomologie (N. S.) 6 (2): 179 - 186." type="journal article" year="1989">Toulgoët (1989)</bibRefCitation>
avec l’espèce 
<taxonomicName id="1F824D14B87CEB039EE2F9BDE6F7C011" authority="Dognin, 1923" authorityName="Dognin" authorityYear="1923" box="[195,492,1610,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Amaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="disconsistens">
<emphasis id="EAF6EA85B87CEB039EE2F9BDE64DC011" box="[195,342,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">A. disconsistens</emphasis>
Dognin, 1923
</taxonomicName>
sp. rev., décrite de 
<collectingRegion id="1A46F875B87CEB039EAFF99DE7EEC0F6" box="[142,245,1641,1668]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">Saõ Paulo</collectingRegion>
de Olivença, province d’Amazonas au 
<collectingCountry id="A0957607B87CEB039E51F97EE7ABC0D6" box="[112,176,1673,1699]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">Brésil</collectingCountry>
. Un séquençage effectué sur des spécimens provenant du 
<collectingCountry id="A0957607B87CEB039D1CFF2FE4A9C687" box="[829,946,216,242]" name="Guatemala" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
au 
<collectingCountry id="A0957607B87CEB039DFAFF2FE302C687" box="[987,1049,216,242]" name="Peru" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">Pérou</collectingCountry>
et de l’État du 
<collectingRegion id="1A46F875B87CEB039C84FF00E414C764" box="[677,783,247,273]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">Rondonia</collectingRegion>
au 
<collectingCountry id="A0957607B87CEB039D12FF00E469C764" box="[819,882,247,273]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">Brésil</collectingCountry>
, a montré que le taxon 
<taxonomicName id="1F824D14B87CEB039A42FF0FE3A1C764" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1901" box="[1123,1210,248,274]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Amaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apyga">
<emphasis id="EAF6EA85B87CEB039A42FF0FE3A1C764" box="[1123,1210,248,274]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">A. apyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
était strictement cantonné en Amérique centrale du 
<collectingCountry id="A0957607B87CEB039CEAFEC0E45BC724" box="[715,832,311,337]" name="Guatemala" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
au 
<collectingCountry id="A0957607B87CEB039D4AFEC0E4FDC724" box="[875,998,311,337]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
. Nous ignorons sur quelles données la décision de mise en synonymie s’est appuyée mais nous la jugeons injustifiée. Nous proposons donc cette réhabilitation.
</paragraph>
